{"archive_sha256":"c32f3905916906521072d045aab7014b7974ca5edce639be731b54d09f8084f7","benchmark":"ArchGym","data_source":"ArchGym","discipline":"Architecture & Microarchitecture","env_type":"chip","instruction":"Complete dse.py so the architecture DSE Pareto selection passes all tests.","prompt":"Implement the Pareto-frontier selection used by a small architecture design-space exploration pass. Complete pareto_frontier() in dse.py. Each candidate has id, latency, energy, and area fields. All three metrics are minimized. A candidate is dominated only when another candidate is no worse in every metric and strictly better in at least one. Return the non-dominated candidate IDs in lexicographic order. Do not mutate the input.","source":{"commit":"53f745af87b256794c0cd712c2b8e77aab74b4a6","paths":["README.md","settings/default_timeloop.yaml"],"repo":"benchmarks/archgym"},"task_files":{"content":"","encoding":"tar.gz+base64"},"task_id":"arch-microarch-archgym-pareto","tools":["python3","pytest"]}
{"archive_sha256":"c50de070d98ef1a9a2c496fc11bc17c4e5ba479eaa6356ab2fee5728488a031f","benchmark":"ChampSim","data_source":"ChampSim","discipline":"Architecture & Microarchitecture","env_type":"chip","instruction":"Complete saturating_counter.h and preserve its public API.","prompt":"Implement the unsigned fixed-width saturating counter in saturating_counter.h. SaturatingCounter<Bits> must support Bits from 1 through 16, clamp constructor values to [0, 2^Bits-1], expose value(), is_min(), and is_max(), and implement prefix/postfix ++ and -- plus += and -= for signed integer deltas. Every operation must saturate without unsigned wraparound. Keep this as a header-only C++20 implementation.","source":{"commit":"51588e1d6f97875fe8de1a3621d28668bff83fcf","paths":["inc/msl/fwcounter.h","test/cpp/src/043-fwcounter.cc"],"repo":"benchmarks/champsim"},"task_files":{"content":"","encoding":"tar.gz+base64"},"task_id":"arch-microarch-champsim-counter","tools":["g++","C++20"]}
{"archive_sha256":"bb584907b3a4d8478681f075fb04964b2bbc54f784ae4ee2326347ecad40af01","benchmark":"Accellera SystemC","data_source":"Accellera SystemC","discipline":"Architecture Modeling","env_type":"chip","instruction":"Implement the SystemC stream accumulator in stream_accumulator.h.","prompt":"Complete stream_accumulator.h as a SystemC module. The module has sc_fifo_in<int> in and sc_fifo_out<int> out ports. Its SC_THREAD must consume input tokens continuously, accumulate each non-overlapping group of four tokens, write one sum for every complete group, then continue with the next group. Do not emit partial groups. Keep the implementation header-only and preserve the class and port names.","source":{"commit":"adb09b1e3f998db9cce702fb8dce22a302c58001","paths":["examples/sysc/simple_fifo/simple_fifo.cpp","examples/sysc/fir/fir.cpp"],"repo":"benchmarks/systemc"},"task_files":{"content":"","encoding":"tar.gz+base64"},"task_id":"architecture-modeling-systemc-stream","tools":["SystemC 3.0.2","g++","pkg-config"]}
{"archive_sha256":"7aea28cbdf06ea48d6e946f7819e5df91095d4f47bbabe2d76fb1a45944ede2a","benchmark":"Timeloop and Accelergy exercises","data_source":"Timeloop and Accelergy exercises","discipline":"Architecture Modeling","env_type":"chip","instruction":"Complete the Timeloop-style architecture description in arch.yaml.","prompt":"Repair arch.yaml to describe the requested weight-stationary accelerator. Keep the existing hierarchy and names. DRAM must be 64 bits wide with 16-bit data words. shared_glb must have depth 16384, 32 banks, and read/write bandwidth 16. PE must be a 16 by 16 spatial mesh. pe_spad must have depth 192, keep Weights, and bypass Inputs and Outputs. mac must use an 8-bit multiplier and 16-bit adder. Replace all null placeholders with these values and leave the file as valid YAML.","source":{"commit":"2d5510807128e9bd5f1cad0705cdf2ec4612fd4e","paths":["workspace/example_designs/example_designs/simple_weight_stationary/arch.yaml"],"repo":"benchmarks/timeloop-accelergy-exercises"},"task_files":{"content":"","encoding":"tar.gz+base64"},"task_id":"architecture-modeling-timeloop-config","tools":["python3","PyYAML","Timeloop architecture schema"]}
{"archive_sha256":"3515cb77f753633d5f88e996c3b71ca7fad7b686f13898be54f360affa84b6bc","benchmark":"RTLLM 2.0","data_source":"RTLLM 2.0","discipline":"RTL Design","env_type":"chip","instruction":"Complete accu.sv with the four-sample valid-gated accumulator.","prompt":"Implement the synthesizable module accu in accu.sv. Ports: clk, active-low asynchronous rst_n, data_in[7:0], valid_in, valid_out, and data_out[9:0]. Accept data_in only on rising clock edges where valid_in is high. For every non-overlapping group of four accepted bytes, drive their 10-bit sum on data_out and pulse valid_out high for exactly one cycle. Invalid cycles must not advance the group. Reset clears partial state and valid_out.","source":{"commit":"41b26896e33b536940116a975626455eed3de65e","paths":["Arithmetic/Accumulator/accu/design_description.txt","Arithmetic/Accumulator/accu/testbench.v","Arithmetic/Accumulator/accu/verified_accu.v"],"repo":"benchmarks/rtllm"},"task_files":{"content":"","encoding":"tar.gz+base64"},"task_id":"rtl-design-rtllm-accumulator","tools":["Icarus Verilog 12","SystemVerilog simulation"]}
{"archive_sha256":"b110639f9d8b06e149b2a8641b211eeeb72c498d572fc87bf175aa98194bf15b","benchmark":"VerilogEval v2","data_source":"VerilogEval v2","discipline":"RTL Design","env_type":"chip","instruction":"Write the complete synthesizable SystemVerilog implementation in TopModule.sv.","prompt":"Implement TopModule in TopModule.sv. Its ports are input clk, input reset, and output logic [3:0] q. It is a decade counter that counts 1 through 10 inclusive. All state changes occur on the positive edge of clk. reset is active-high and synchronous and sets q to 1. After q reaches 10, the next active clock edge wraps it to 1.","source":{"commit":"c498220d0a52248f8e3fdffe279075215bde2da6","paths":["dataset_spec-to-rtl/Prob035_count1to10_prompt.txt","dataset_spec-to-rtl/Prob035_count1to10_test.sv","dataset_spec-to-rtl/Prob035_count1to10_ref.sv"],"repo":"benchmarks/verilog-eval"},"task_files":{"content":"","encoding":"tar.gz+base64"},"task_id":"rtl-design-verilogeval-counter","tools":["Icarus Verilog 12","SystemVerilog simulation"]}
{"archive_sha256":"e328d6d48d8941845a9a74924005918732f3b3c94d3e97a361792ba5ff0c72a3","benchmark":"OpenTitan","data_source":"OpenTitan","discipline":"Software Development","env_type":"chip","instruction":"Complete the portable OpenTitan-style CRC32 implementation in crc32.c.","prompt":"Implement crc32.c using the API in crc32.h. It must compute reflected IEEE 802.3 CRC-32 with polynomial 0xedb88320 and match Python zlib.crc32. Support one-shot crc32(), streaming init/add8/add32/add/finish, zero-length buffers, and unaligned buffers. crc32_add32 must consume the word in little-endian byte order regardless of host alignment. Do not use zlib or a lookup-table dependency.","source":{"commit":"b583fba84cfd9603694abab6a1f8e97cf2cfcd19","paths":["sw/device/lib/base/crc32.c","sw/device/lib/base/crc32.h","sw/device/lib/base/crc32_functest.c"],"repo":"benchmarks/opentitan"},"task_files":{"content":"","encoding":"tar.gz+base64"},"task_id":"software-opentitan-crc32","tools":["gcc","C11"]}
{"archive_sha256":"56013c93b615756651774dedce0dd8800c2c20c4d3602c4249b9a58d92932ef7","benchmark":"Zephyr RTOS","data_source":"Zephyr RTOS","discipline":"Software Development","env_type":"chip","instruction":"Complete min_heap.c as a portable Zephyr-style fixed-storage heap.","prompt":"Implement the fixed-storage generic min-heap API in min_heap.c. Elements are opaque fixed-size byte records ordered by the caller comparator. Implement init, push, peek, pop, remove by zero-based heap-array index, and find. Push and removal must preserve heap order in O(log n); find may be O(n). Return -1 when full, false for invalid removal or empty pop, and never allocate memory. Preserve the API in min_heap.h and correctly support element sizes that are not machine-word sized.","source":{"commit":"3df5fa4d3fcf664373ffa64b88975ffe2f3a6b68","paths":["include/zephyr/sys/min_heap.h","tests/lib/min_heap/src/test_min_heap.c","samples/data_structures/min-heap/src/main.c"],"repo":"benchmarks/zephyr"},"task_files":{"content":"","encoding":"tar.gz+base64"},"task_id":"software-zephyr-min-heap","tools":["gcc","C11"]}
{"archive_sha256":"75ea9d7a4395ddc80d7aa26d7dceb5f9334c4a3aa64915f23933263e4dfbd49a","benchmark":"YosysHQ MCY","data_source":"YosysHQ MCY","discipline":"Verification (DV/FV)","env_type":"chip","instruction":"Write a mutation-sensitive self-checking testbench in bitcnt_tb.sv.","prompt":"Complete bitcnt_tb.sv as a self-checking SystemVerilog testbench for bitcnt.v. The DUT implements CLZ64, CLZ32, CTZ64, CTZ32, CNT64, and CNT32 selected by din_func 000 through 101. Verify every operation, including all-zero inputs and the rule that 32-bit modes ignore din_data[63:32]. The testbench module must be named testbench, print PASS on success, call $fatal on a mismatch, and finish. The verifier will run it against the reference design and mutation variants.","source":{"commit":"686c816ceaae60003d51a863e0aefe221003185c","paths":["examples/bitcnt/bitcnt.v","examples/bitcnt/bitcnt_tb.v","examples/bitcnt/test_fm.sv"],"repo":"benchmarks/mcy"},"task_files":{"content":"","encoding":"tar.gz+base64"},"task_id":"verification-mcy-bitcnt","tools":["Icarus Verilog 12","mutation testing"]}
{"archive_sha256":"c0472f7740cf8b2a0bebf024d5c9e9b8bf238ee009706c9164a9eb5e200a50ee","benchmark":"riscv-formal methodology","data_source":"riscv-formal methodology","discipline":"Verification (DV/FV)","env_type":"chip","instruction":"Complete properties.sv with exhaustive combinational FIFO assertions.","prompt":"Write immediate formal properties in properties.sv for a depth-2 FIFO transition relation. The file is included inside formal_top and may reference count[1:0], wr_en, rd_en, and next_count[1:0]. Inputs are unconstrained except that the harness assumes count <= 2. Add at least four assertions proving: next_count never exceeds 2; a write without a read is blocked when full; a read without a write is blocked when empty; and simultaneous read/write preserves count. Use an always @* block and no module declaration.","source":{"commit":"c992aa61fdfe0846c5ed90324c596202a1c69b76","paths":["README.md","cores/picorv32/checks.cfg","cores/picorv32/complete.sv"],"repo":"benchmarks/riscv-formal"},"task_files":{"content":"","encoding":"tar.gz+base64"},"task_id":"verification-riscv-formal-properties","tools":["Yosys 0.59.1","SAT proof"]}
